== List of vessels ==

I have added the names of builders and construction dates for the majority of these vessels. I have also changed the pennant numbers for those vessels built in the UK and transferred to the Royal Canadian Navy, as they were referenced under their RN names but their RCN pennant numbers! Please note that all pennant numbers were changed along with their names when the vessels were transferred to the RCN. [[User:Rif Winfield|Rif Winfield]] ([[User talk:Rif Winfield|talk]]) 05:30, 28 April 2009 (UTC)

== "Bridgenorth Castle"? ==

I can't be sure so haven't edited, but if this ship was intended to be named after the place in Shropshire, then it should be ''Bridgnorth'', without an E. [[User:Loganberry|Loganberry]] ([[User talk:Loganberry|Talk]]) 15:54, 4 May 2009 (UTC)

==What's the use of long list of individual cancelled ship details ?==
